name: Good Friends Restaurant & Cafe
address: 55, Jalan SS 15/8a, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Jennifer Wen
reviews.text: 05.01.2025 Sunday my very first time here. I ordered the fried chicken waffle and it was nice. The waffle was nicely done, light crispy on the outside and soft on the inside. The chicken tender was just alright for me. But it was dry and lack of taste. Somehow over fried a little. Hazelnut latte was alright too. For a cup cost RM14, I would expect the taste to be more fragrant and slightly bigger in size too. Yes it is an expensive restaurant. Just a breakfast and it cost RM48.40.

reviews.author: mustang sox
reviews.text:
The coffee beans served was good. Recommend to try its cold brew Dutch coffee. 7.2/10

However, the chicken teriyaki soba wasn't that good. The teriyaki sauce was too light and bland. The soba was too dry. 4.4/10

The Crme Brle banana brown sugar was an interesting fusion, but it didn't had the caramelised top and the too soft. 4/10

Nice comfy restaurant with cheerful staff.

reviews.author: P J
reviews.text:
This place reminds me of my ahmas house - super chill and cozy vibes. Okay, maybe my ahmas place isnt as aesthetic as this one, haha, but still!

I tried their pesto and it was so good! Nicely balanced, not too salty or bland - just right for my taste. Friendly services! Definitely planning to visit again!

name: The Great Cafe | Excitement in Every Bite
address: 33, Jln SS 15/2A, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Harsrey
reviews.text: Had lunch at The Great Cafe today and really enjoyed it! Ordered their fried rice with karaage chicken, and it was delicious-crispy, flavorful, and perfectly paired. Also tried their English muffin set, which was just as good. Great food and a nice spot for a meal!

reviews.author: M Mus
reviews.text: I love this place. My favourite cafe. Food is amazing and coffee is decent. Try the nasi goreng and nasi lemak. I bring my kids sometimes and they enjoy the food and the toys that they kept there. The staff are amazing. Very tolerant to my kids and friendly. Keep up the good work. Will always promote and patronise this place.

reviews.author: MFH - Malaysia Food Hunter
reviews.text:
Visit date: 30/1/2024

Simple interior with lots of natural lighting. Service was great and everything is reasonably priced.

They have 3 breakfast combos and 30% for coffee till 12pm. Good place for work. Theres free water and WiFi.

The toast looks very simple but oh so good  It taste like theres caramel in the spread. The signature chicken ramen (RM13.90) was surprisingly tasty and well portioned too. Pandan nasi lemak (RM10.90) was worth-it, good portion and yummy.

Some description and pricing on the menu are a little confusing like how its an additional RM1 for ramen noodle when the picture shows ramen noodle and as for the nasi lemak, it actually comes with fried egg and chicken patty but its not mentioned instead its stated that for egg and patty, they are additional charges. Kinda confusing for us and we ended up having 2 patties and 2 fried eggs for the nasi lemak which was unnecessary. Perhaps owners can relook into the wordings of the menu and amend them.

Other than that, everything was great. Place is clean, especially the toilet  , food was yummy and service was prompt and good. Recommended!

name: Pak Edy Cafe
address: 8, Jalan SS 19/1d, Ss 19, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: EG LF
reviews.text: The place is clean and owner is humble. Food quality is good! However can't comment much visited the place between business meeting for touch and go lunch.

reviews.author: checkmate
reviews.text: Ok but not enough staff most of restaurants really need assistance n staff

reviews.author: Fahmy Ameer
reviews.text: Good service and price berpatutan

name: Benjy Cafe
address: E-Tiara, Jalan Kemajuan Subang, Ss 16, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: kykoh500
reviews.text:
Quiet place. Few people only. Maybe it was a weekday.
The food were served one by one and it came out hot, from the oven/stove.
The mushroom soup was good.
The lamb shank was wonderful except it still had the raw lamb  taste. The chicken chop was unusual. It was layered with a full round pineapple and an egg on the top. Well marinated and wonderful combination. The salmon fish was good.

reviews.author: Jeremie Ting
reviews.text: We revisited the Cafe since the last visit in December 2020. We ordered flat lobster chowder, wild mushroom soup, pan fried garlic butter fish (served on mash potato with almond slice, roasted cherry tomatoes & garlic butter sauce), and grilled juicy chicken thigh and shrimps accompanied with Chef's BBQ sauce, and served with a side of sauted mushrooms, vegetables and a heap of mash potatoes. The space inside is a bit tight, although there are tables just outside, The food was tasty and nice, including both soups. The bill came to RM200 for the four of us.

reviews.author: Yen Him Ho
reviews.text:
I found this restaurant from Google Map review having high rating.

Food came out very fast 10 minutes after order.

The salmon steak is a huge cut, nicely cooked to perfection with slightly crispy skin & tender meat.

The sauted vegetable is fresh & juicy, with less salt so the rich natural taste is enhanced!

Salad is fresh with very nice light sauce.

Apple crumble is delicious, rich in apple & cinnamon, slight to the sweet side but just nice is taken with vanilla ice cream.

Overall will invite friends for lunch/dinner here.

name: Nasir Cafe
address: Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Eleazar Joey
reviews.text:
Good: At least the "teh ais" that I ordered tasted good despite being on the pricier side

Bad: You'll expect that a stall inside a mosque premise would charge you cheaper (takkan pihak masjid kenakan sewa yang mahal seperti premis yang terletak di kawasan rumah kedai SS15) but that isn't the case here, the takeaway "teh ais" I ordered cost RM2.50 which is similar in price; if not more expensive than a proper Mamak stall / restaurant

Ugly: None that I can think of at the moment as I haven't tried any of their food yet

reviews.author: Fazrul jalaluddin
reviews.text: My go-to place while waiting for kid to finish school. The prices for food here are affordable, food portion is ok. People here are friendly, i can get the 'warong kampung' feel here, which is nice!

reviews.author: mmfirdaus mfm
reviews.text: Simple, fast, tasty & cheap.

name: Jibby & Co
address: GK-11, Ground Floor, Empire Shopping Gallery, Jalan SS 16/1, Ss 16, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Azhani Azizi
reviews.text:
The food was delicious - nothing mind blowing though for the price you pay for. It was delicious but for that price, you'd expect it to be a lot better. However, the food was beautifully plated and well balanced.

We booked a few days prior and we had no issues with our orders except for the fact that our meals were a little cold because they prepared it a little too early.

The atmosphere was nice with the decorations. Lunch hour was packed with office people, full house perhaps at one point. Parking was easy and the staffs were friendly.

reviews.author: Sean Tan
reviews.text: I quite liked the Thai Beef Ribs here. It was tender and delicious. But everything else wasn't nice, like the lamb shank, which was tender, but way too sweet. The eggs benedict thing was weird and not nice. The environment was one of the best for cafes, being quite modern and contemporary, with a touch of nature. The service was also not good, being less than minimal. The things here are way too expensive. The lamb shank was 85ringgit and wasn't even nice. Overall definitely not recommend.

reviews.author: nicholas y
reviews.text: We ordered a lamb pizza, duck aglio olio and chicken parmigiana carbonara. All three of them were commendable. Their service here was truly remarkable. Among them was one of the waiters called Jay, who was incredibly attentive and polite! The ambience was really nice too.

name: Three Plates Full
address: 57, Jln SS 15/4E, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: edwin tan
reviews.text:
Had a Lovely dinner lovely.

We had only 2 plates between the 2 of us and we were already full so it isnt really 3 plates full :))

They recommended the ribs and it was tasty

They had a sangria promo and it was good too! One of the better ones around!

The pork collar was super tender and the sauce excellent.

The service is on point too! You dont have to ask for plain water, they serve it to you! Plus they keep refilling your empty cup.

Very well trained staff and the server will always be happy to give you a recommendation.

Was too full to take the dessert. But we will definitely be back to try it and the rest of the menu

reviews.author: Jia Pin Lee
reviews.text:
Great services, especially by the staff at the payment counter. Very friendly and accommodating.

Ordered the lasagna and mac and cheese. Both were quite good. The lasagna was cheesy and not oily. You can taste each layer nicely. The mac and cheese was crispy, not too salty, and cheesy. Both the foods were balanced in taste. Not sure why they were using plastic cup instead of glass, though, for drinks.

reviews.author: Wyne Teo
reviews.text:
Reserved a table of 10 for my sons birthday. The staff answered my call with very warm welcome, from there they gave me a positive first impression.

This place is a good choice if you plan to have a gathering. Comfortable atmosphere and delicious food.

We ordered in total 10 dishes and my guests are all satisfied with the meals. The food taste good and portion just nice. The staffs are attentive and always ready to accommodate to our requests.

name: Kueh Cafe  Subang Jaya
address: 11G, Jalan SS 18/1b, Ss18, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Jennifer Wen
reviews.text: 03.01.2025 Friday. My 1st time here. Bring my mom here for breakfast. We were the first customer at 8am. We had the iced cappuccino which was just ok. The nasi tomato with ayam masak merah was good. I like the ayam masak merah, meat was tender, juicy and spicy. Roti Jala with curry chicken was alright. Curry texture was watery though and not rich in flavor. Staff at cashier was polite and smiley. Staff serving food to our table was expressionless. We said thank you and she ignored. Overall good 1st time experience. Nice songs being played. Comfortable and clean environment.

reviews.author: Simon Choy
reviews.text:
A very unique take on warong styled casual dining experience within. This place puts it several notches higher compared to what you typically encounter from the street or shopping malls. The ambience within is relaxed and unrushed, absolutely fantastic.

If there's one thing really good here asides from their large selection of kuih muih, it's the freshly made-to-order teh and kopi beverages. The drinks are an almost perfect compliment to whatever dish you have ordered from the menu. Come around for late breakfast or brunch and make an order for fresh lempeng, a savoury pancake like snack served with sambal ikan bilis. It, is, to die for. Warmly recommended whenever life gets too hectic outside and you need a brief getaway from the rush.

reviews.author: ARIFF SHAH KHAIRUDDIN
reviews.text: First time here. Nasi lemak costs me RM5.90 and the lempeng with sambal daging costs me RM7.90 a bit expensive. Nasi lemak tastes good with the sambal a bit of spicy and sweet. Kueh tasted good. Definitely will repeat again

name: Kedai Kopi Malaya @ NU Empire
address: No UG-02, Empire Mall, Jalan SS 16/1, Ss 16, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Jerilynn Ng
reviews.text: Disappointing experience. The half-boiled eggs were completely overdone-which defeats the point of ordering them that way. On top of that, they used margarine instead of butter for the toast, which gave it a greasy, artificial taste. For a place that claims to offer traditional kopitiam fare, the quality fell far short.

reviews.author: CH LIM
reviews.text:
Just sit down while waiting  surprising the curry mee was quite good. Broth is thick with the right flavors for a curry mee. KL curry mee flavor if you are curious, not penang or ipoh :), with chicken shred, long beans, tauge, taufu pok, egg, and mini prawn. i prefer with curry chicken though.
Promotion during lunch time, order one food and free drinks.
No comments on the service and atmosphere cause it is like a pop up store.
Located just outside Mdm Kwan

reviews.author: News Lemak
reviews.text:
Got fly in the Asam Laksa. Cashier refuses to take responsibility.

He say he wont do anything about it.

name: KHENG WAH Restaurant
address: G-03, SS15 Courtyard, Jln SS 15/4G, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: AwesomeGeekGear
reviews.text:
Came here looking for cheese baked rice and was not too bad although portions were slightlysmaller than what I'm used to at other places.

The garlic sauce chicken chop cheese baked rice was not bad to be honest. It's considerably dry but the cheese provides a good texture. The chicken was a little disappointing as it was small and thin. As you eat it does start to feel a little more salty.

The other we tried was the bacon prawn with black pepper sauce which surprised me cause it was actually sweet. Not exactly to my liking but it could appeal to those who would prefer it that way.

The staff were not attentive as after I ordered I didn't not get any physical confirmation that my order was received. Some of the staff were also arguing with each other halfway through my meal which was a turn off.

reviews.author: Deadpool
reviews.text: No wait (although it's PH) 4pm. It's self order by scanning QR code. The only service is staff sending food to our table. Place is clean, warm lighting, at times irs hot when the glass door open (hot air rushes in). Food is nice except toast as its too oily (bread drench in butter). Price is reasonable. MUST EAT their chilli oil (it's so good, crunchy n tasty).

reviews.author: LONG Chai Meng
reviews.text:
Saturday 5 April 2025 - came here for lunch with a friend. Good place to rest and relax. Food is good. Service is also quite fast.

Order food through QR code. There is a printed menu.

Very nice environment.

name: Canai 15 Cafe (SS15)
address: 2, Jalan SS 15/4, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Colin Thong
reviews.text: Visited for late breakfast. One of your cleaner, halal 'mamak' restaurants. Corner lot which catches a good breeze. Had a maggi goreng - not as spicy and salty as you would normally - taugeh, sawi and carrots over cabbage for a change but missing the diced taufu cubes, imho. Very interestingly priced, i.e. ramah-like, set lunches. Ironically, my simple meal cost much higher, which made me enquire to which i received no response. Oh well...

reviews.author: AISYY MOHD
reviews.text: I got my lunch to go from Canai SS15. Now they are selling chicken rice! It comes with a good portion, a good price, and a drink as part of the set!  The roasted chicken tastes so good! It's a quick lunch to grab if you're in the SS15 area!

reviews.author: Sunny Sin Chakrabarty
reviews.text: Honestly, it's pretty hard to find a flaw here. The food is delicious always, well seasoned and a variety of options. I've had desi cuisine here that I had never tasted before. The staff are so friendly and kind, ensuring you have a wonderful experience. The decor is so cozy and whoever is in charge of the playlist that plays when I'm there, needs a promotion! The music accompanies your taste buds!

name: Upstairs Caf
address: First Floor, 12A, Jalan SS 12/1b, Ss 12, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Nur Shamsiah
reviews.text: Love the food here. I really enjoy the taste and plan to come again. The dessert also suit my taste too. some of it got a little bit sweet but it is okay for me.

reviews.author: Farah Isza
reviews.text: It was my first time in here. The entrance is cute. Get the vibe here. The counter is clear with their menu. Easy to choose. Try their Aglio Olio Chicken and kinda like it. Can add chili flakes if you want. They put it on a separate counter. The seats are quite comfy but limited. Came around 730pm after work, and there are a lot of people. Got outdoor sits at the balcony, too.

reviews.author: shafinaz hasan
reviews.text:
I love the vibe here, and the staff are also nice. Its a great spot for anyone who wants to work from cafe or study. They offer different seating options, including some with plug sockets, and theres also an outdoor space(I loveeeee)

I ordered the carbonara and smashed burger, along with iced chocolate and peach tea. I really enjoyed the smashed burger and their peach tea, so refreshing! Id definitely come back to try more from the menu and for the vibe again!

name: The Cafe 35
address: JVCO Group Office, Ss 12, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Mi O
reviews.text:
Overall Experience:
The Caf 35 is a cozy and quiet spot inside the hospital. Its clean and comfortable, making it a good place to take a break and enjoy a meal. Complimentary fruit-infused water is available, which adds a refreshing touch to the dining experience.

Food:
The menu offers both local and Western options. I tried the eggs benedict and omelet set - both were tasty, fresh, and served in large portions. The salad on the side was a nice touch.

Service:
The staff were friendly and the service was smooth, with food served quickly.

Cost: $~$$
The price is reasonable, with meals starting from RM13 to RM17, considering the big portions and variety of choices available.

reviews.author: Desmond Leong
reviews.text:
Had breakfast at The Cafe 35 at SJMC Subang Jaya, and it was a pleasant experience!

What we ordered:
1.	Lontong (RM13): Generous portion and delicious-worth trying.
2.	Poached Egg with Hollandaise Sauce (RM16): Good portion, but the egg was overly sour due to too much vinegar in the poaching water.
3.	Eggs with Sauted Mushrooms and Cherry Tomatoes (RM17): Huge portion, tasted great, and I highly recommend this dish!

Overall:
	The prices are very reasonable, especially compared to the food court behind Starbucks.
	Bonus: Free flow of detox water!
	The environment is clean and comfortable, making it a great spot for a relaxed breakfast.

Will definitely visit again for the good value and cozy setting!

reviews.author: LarryKoh
reviews.text: Been there three times for lunch , environment is cozy and chill . The food quality is good , overall it is not too salty or oily. Their lunch set is Indian cuisine   , curry tastes good .  The price is cafe price . Even during lunch time is full of people but there are enough seats . Is a good choice for a meal inside the hospital.

name: BlackBixon Cafe & Restaurant - Nu Empire Shopping Gallery
address: Lot G23A & G25, Nu Empire Shopping Gallery, Jalan SS 16/1, SS16, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Vickey Chen
reviews.text:
Black sourdough 
Healthy options 
Generous portions 
Lots of good options here from light eaters, vegetarians to heartier meals and big eaters.

Dishes are colourful too. Love the salads - a good mix of vegetables and micro greens.

Burgers are good, too.
Would love to try the fish and chips next time - looks good.

Comfortable place and good service, too. Staff is always smiling and sweet.
Pastries look good as well - I liked the matcha pistachio yum, with cakes from Elevete available.

Theres a tea time specials as well. New promos now and then. Cant get bored.

reviews.author: Salina Salli
reviews.text:
Food was nice enough. but the portion is small considering the price. Ordered the chilli soft shell crab pasta recommended. Very nice

The chicken schnitzel was a bit overcooked, the side salad dressing was light, simple and nice but the salad not sure what greens it was  a bit too hard i guess it was kale . the side mashed potatoes was very well done.

Food was were served fast enough however i think not wait staff was not hard to find so better asked for everything when they were serving you

reviews.author: Gerry Leong
reviews.text: Checked this place out for the first time today. Tried their signature Black Fried Chicken and Soft Shell Crab pasta. Food is pretty decent but the fried chicken is a little hard to my liking but overall taste is decent. Noticed their pastries are looking good. Will give them a try soon.

name: RATA Restaurant
address: 25, Jalan SS 15/5a, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Q Wei Ern
reviews.text: Celebrated Mothers Day here. Have got a free cake and that was lovely. Food was generally above average but I do find them being cold when served. I hope that it could be more warm.

reviews.author: Sures Packirisamy
reviews.text: Been here many times. One of our favorite restaurants in Subang Jaya. The food and drinks are tasty. The portion is generous. They introduce a mocktail today called Pineapple Tamarind Cooler, I fall in love with the drink and ordered twice. I highly recommend this drink for those who are teetotaler. Leanne did a very good job and she is very friendly and helpful as well.  Way to go

reviews.author: Kia Sen Tan
reviews.text: Went there for happy hour with my son.  Ordered bucket of warsteiner beer, 3 mugs of Guinness draught and karaage as finger food.   Cant comment much on the food but the menu shows very good variety.   The German beer were okay, need to drink it a bit slow to taste the malt which is quite fragrance.  Guinness are not as creamy as expected compared to Healy Mac but I would say nowadays there very few beer outlet with good Guinness.   Karaage were acceptable but the the cutting were too small making it unlike typical good Karaage that we have.  However, the dipping condiments were pretty good hence making the chicken acceptable to us.  Will probably be back for more cuisine experience in future as this place really have quite a lot of regulars.

name: Big Family Restaurant
address: 4 & 6, 2, Jalan SS 15/4b, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Chuah W Pang
reviews.text: This is definitely one of the cleanest Chinese coffee shop in Subang Jaya. It has indoor outdoor seating. The ventilation is pretty good. The wantan mee here is very nice. The coffee here is also exceptional. Service is good and staffs are friendly. Th the curry. Mee though is below average, it has too much MSG, it made me feel very unwell after taking hope the owner improves  by reducing MSG. I generally dont put such a remark, but this is pretty obvious.

reviews.author: Sue Chuah
reviews.text:
Hidden gem for char koey teow lovers!
Just a short walk from SS15 LRT station, this food court is a true find. The Penang-style char koey teow here is on another level-intense wok hei, crispy pork lard, ultra-thin Chinese sausage, juicy prawns, and generous siham (cockles) all come together in one flavour-packed plate.

The local coffee here super good as well.

The space is clean and comfortable, with both air-conditioned and fan seating. With over 40 stalls offering everything from local favourites to international dishes, there's something for everyone.

My family keeps coming back for breakfast, lunch, dinner, and even supper because the variety caters to all tastes, and it's open daily from 8am to 2am!

reviews.author: alwyn
reviews.text:
ngau lam min, char kuey teow and grilled fish are the reliable options here.  ditto sotong kangkung, stuffed taufu. and the xiangla jiaozi.

kolo mee and mee pok are good, in sense that anything with that much lard can't be bed.  stereo oink in this case, with both oleaginuous and granular forms kicking in.

hongkong-style beef noodles are tasty enough.  moo payload is has heft and includes entire rack of spare parts, but is also chewy.  so possibility of buffalo rather than beef here.  that said, nothing wrong with eating tractor.

kai si hor fun is good eating, but is problematic.  butchery is sloppy and leaves behind bone shards in the soup.  poh piah is too dry, which doesn't work with the crumbly and crunchy elements of its payload.

burgers are good, and a welcome addition.  preparation, which includes a blow-torch treatment, is meticulous.  signature bacon-double-oink is melt-in-mouth good eating.  unfortunately it also crumbles in hand, so eat in situ with cutlery.

chasiu ramen is not up to the mark.  broth lacks flavour or depth, and liau freshness.

name: Bang Ga Bang Ga  Korean Restaurant
address: No. 19-G (Ground Floor, Jalan SS15/4, SS15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Jeremie Ting
reviews.text: In our inaugural visit, we ordered spicy beef bul go gi that comes with free refill of kimchi, radish pickle, and soup. We also ordered ala carte medium dak gang jeong that comes with a choice of two flavours, and we selected soy bean and butter garlic, and also rose flavoured tteok bok ki, together with Korean tea that also comes with free refill. In addition, we also ordered takeaway a medium dak gang jeong (soy sauce and original flavour). The food was satisfactory. The bill came to RM98.30 for the three of us, plus takeaway.

reviews.author: Henry Erik Estrada
reviews.text: Authentic Korean resto with decent pricing. The menu is not that many, but all the food we tried tasted good and authentic. Service is normal, took a while before the food served upon ordering. Usually crowded with college students. I deduct 1 star due to no complimentary water for drink options like any other authentic Korean resto. Parking is difficul as this is SS15. All in all a recommended place to eat if you crave Korean food

reviews.author: Immie Syazreen
reviews.text: Second time here.. food was great and cheap for a Korean restaurant. Service was good and fast too. Location can still be improved. Aircond doesnt seem to be cold enough as the table was so close to each other you can feel lil bit stuffy. But for a quick, tasty Korean lunch should be fine.

name: Lao Jia Xiao Guan Restaurant
address: 1, Jalan SS 14/1, Ss 14, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Harmonie Lai
reviews.text: The salad and lemongrass chicken chop were great-good portion size and affordable price, especially given the quality ingredients and taste. The thoughtful and attentive lady boss always makes me happy to return.

reviews.author: Cheng Shiau Ling
reviews.text: Nice western food in a shop lot. Love the fresh vege with sweet citrus taste. The fries taste good too. Most importantly, the ingredients are fresh!

reviews.author: Lee Kim Eng
reviews.text: Ordered black pepper lamb chop. Big portion, salad is fresh.

name: Terazza Brasserie Restaurant
address: Jalan SS 12/1, Ss 12, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Eu Xin Hong
reviews.text:
Fancy atmosphere, friendly and knowledgeable staffs.

The main dish such as rice with veggies/meats are decent. Cakes are nice but portion a bit small, pastries just meh
Mostly takeaway through ReMeal app making the price somewhat reasonable.

However be aware of limited parking during events and costly parkings.

reviews.author: Adriel Wong
reviews.text: Had a year-end work lunch here, and my colleagues and I had a good time overall. The food is decent with a reasonably sized spread. The main attraction is the competitive pricing. It's probably one of the more affordable buffets you can find in the area. While you will find better spreads in other hotels, you will get your money's worth here. The restaurant itself is set up nicely. It isn't the most spacious, so it can get quite crowded if there are many people around. If you want a buffet meal with a group or team and are on a budget, I would  recommend Terraza Brasserie.

reviews.author: Veron Sin
reviews.text:
Understated and splendid spread. The way I word my review below, you may think I am sponsored (but I am not. The spread just exceeded my expectations)

The spread is not big, but the ingredients used are decent and quality. Fresh too!

Seafood: scallops are huge, juicy and fresh

Mains: Pilaf rice was so fragrant I took 4 rounds, against my no-carb buffet policy. Carbonara sauce was creamy and rich. The assam fish had bite to it

Salad counter: awesome smoked duck salad, amongst other great mix.

Carving and meat station: Grilled beef had fats that almost melts in your mouth? Can't believe it coming from a hotel not many ppl talk about. Love the roast lamb and duck too. The grilled skewered prawns was so fresh!

Soup: pumpkin soup was sweet and tasted nourishing. Love it.

Desserts: Favourite was the chocolate fountain and the bread pudding. Simply amazing.

Drinks: thoughtful infused water instead of the usual sugary drinks.

Well done Terazza team. Very thoughtful spread and service. Keep it up. Will be back to support when I am over my food coma.

name: Restoran Oregi
address: 53, Jalan SS 15/4b, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Sheldon Vinsent
reviews.text: One of the OG spots in SS 15. The lamb mandy was delicious and they gave quite a good portion. Would have preferred if they used basmati rice instead of the normal ome though. Also, the restaurant feels very old and even the menu looks dated. In short, the shop could use some sprucing up.

reviews.author: Edmund JP
reviews.text: The Arabian food here was fantastic. The lamb was tender. Absolutely love it. The service was good and friendly too. The taste was absolutely delicious. Parking is a problem in this commercial square, but it is not impossible. Highly recommend the lamb stew and the signature lamb rice (that looks like a burger from the menu photo)

reviews.author: Croco Tai
reviews.text: Good service and tasty food, recommended. If you have a large appetite you can go for their LARGE spaghetti  Yummy

name: Shangrila Bistro & Kitchen
address: 19, Jalan SS 15/4b, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Abbie Tok
reviews.text:
Amazing and delicious food and the dessert was so unique! A mixture of ice cream, fruits and apple pie! FANTASTIC!! Thank you the superb hospitality!
Definitely a must-visit bistro when you are in Malaysia!

reviews.author: Prabagar Woon
reviews.text:
NEVER EVER EAT HERE! I was here as recent as 25th Jan with my family of 6. We all ordered different food choices. 4 western and 2 asian, 2 of which came after 30 mins and the rest more than an hour! Whats funny was there was nobody else in the place! We came here baseD on a facebook recommendation and we were there just before 9pm. we left 10.30pm disappointed like never before in our lives! Even their drinks order was taken incorrectly such sprite, coke and water! Billing was incorrect as well. We were very patient because of my aunt who is a heart and pressure patient ... or else I would have given them a true piece of my mind!
NEVER GO HERE UNLESS THE INTENTION IS TO HAVE ALCOHOL! But then again I can't guarantee the quality as well as we never had any.... deplorable food quality and service!

reviews.author: Kesawan Munisamy
reviews.text: Small and cozy place with good food.

name: JIBRIL SS15
address: 25, Jalan SS 15/4b, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia
editorial_summary: Funky cafe showcasing meat & seafood offerings with salted egg sauce, plus steak, pasta & mocktails.

reviews.author: Randy Wan
reviews.text:
Tried JIBRIL SS15 in Subang and, to be fair, the food was genuinely tasty. From the lobster to the chicken, pasta, sotong and fries-every dish hit the mark flavour-wise. No complaints there. Clearly, the kitchen knows what its doing once the food arrives.

The issue? The waiting time. We waited nearly 20-30 minutes per dish, and they arrived one by one like they were on their own little parade. What shouldve been a 15-minute kitchen job turned into a full-on endurance test. By the time the last plate came, I was more full of frustration than food.

Is it worth the wait? For me, not really. I came hungry, not for a slow-burn food reveal. But if youve got time to kill and the patience of a saint, the food wont let you down.

reviews.author: Busyra Aisyah
reviews.text:
I had such a wonderful experience dining here! From the moment I stepped in, the atmosphere was calm and relaxing - the perfect spot to unwind, whether youre with friends or just having some alone time. The concept of the place was cozy yet modern, making it feel warm and welcoming.

The staff were incredibly friendly and attentive. They greeted us with smiles and went out of their way to be helpful. Service was top-notch and impressively fast - we didnt have to wait long for our food at all.

We ordered their signature butter chicken and the baked rice, and it was absolutely delicious. The cheese was perfectly melted, and the sauce was rich and flavorful - comfort food at its best. For dessert, we had vanilla ice cream. It was smooth, creamy, and just the right amount of sweetness to end the meal on a high note.

Overall, it wasnt just about the food - it was the whole experience. Great ambiance, amazing service, and food that hits the spot. Definitely a place Id come back to and recommend to others!

reviews.author: Ajai MN
reviews.text: The food and ambience at this restaurant are quite nice - the dishes were well-prepared and the atmosphere was pleasant. However, the location is not ideal, with limited parking available, which made getting there a bit stressful. Additionally, the strong smell of perfume inside was overwhelming and gave me a headache, which affected my overall dining experience. It's a good spot if you can overlook these drawbacks, but some improvements are definitely needed.

name: Rizki Cafe
address: B-G, RIZKI CAFE, CASA TIARA SERVIS APARTMENT, 12, Jalan SS 16/1, Ss 16, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: MH Sunny
reviews.text: VERY GOOD FOOD

name: Restoran SS13 New Sea View
address: G7, G8 & G9, Grand Subang, Jalan SS13/3, Subang Jaya Industrial Estate, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Cheehaw Choong
reviews.text: Cant believe I found such a high-quality, self-invented chicken chop recipe at a hawker stall!** The slow-braised chicken is incredibly tender, topped with a fragrant herb-garlic crust for extra crunch. The meat stays juicy with a perfect texture. The rich brown sauce and creamy mashed potato are the best Ive ever had, while the pickled sesame cabbage adds a refreshing balance to the dish.

reviews.author: Racheal Tan
reviews.text:
Heaps of good & yummy looking food here. I love especially their Herb Crusted Chicken. It is healthy yet delicious. I for one, who hates chicken breast but their dish has changed my taste buds. Soft and juicy chicken breast, creamy mashed potatoes and cabbage on the side.

Extremely well seasoned and to me, it was the perfect portion.

The best part about this stall is that, they made everything from scratch including their gravy. It is a MUST GET! MUST TRY! Meal.

reviews.author: Veronica Chuah
reviews.text: This hawker stalls herbs chicken breast chop is a game-changer! As someone who usually avoids chicken breast, I was blown away by how tender and flavorful it was. Perfect for gym buffs craving a healthy, protein-packed meal thats delicious too. Highly recommend.

name: WARTEK SS15
address: 10, Jalan SS 15/8b, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Sandy  (Bunny Wei)
reviews.text:
Halal.
The place is clean, comfy and cosy.
Staff is a bit preoccupied on the phone on personal calls. Some staffs replied with an attitude.
Overall food is good. Bebek is crispy and yummy.
Highly recommend the Bebek Madura.
Sambal chilli is not for the weak.
Eat at your own risk.

reviews.author: Aida Hazera
reviews.text: First lunch experience. The dish had potential, but didnt quite hit the mark for me. The only enjoyable is gulai tunjang. Nasi uduk is okay. Daging belado was unfortunately on the tougher side, safe to say hard like rock i can knock it on the table. The dish lack the heat i was hoping for; not spicy at all.

reviews.author: Andy Low
reviews.text: Nasi Udut is nice. Bebek is crispy. But there are quite a number of dishes is not available. Some items in the menu stated only available in Ara branch

name: Q Bistro SS15
address: Lot No, 103, Jalan SS 15/4c, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: alwyn
reviews.text:
good outlet of a good chain.  nice selection of proteins, but somewhat short on the vegetables.

ayam bawang is particularly good.  they're piled high in an aromatic pile, high as an elephant's eye, at the start of shift.  ditto house special ayam q, if you like the less messy dry rub style.

watch what you pile on, lest you suffer sticker shock.  chicken is the safest option, sotong is dangerous.  prices are displayed on the buffet line, so you only have yourself to blame if you get burnt.

can't go wrong with any of the rotis on offer.  beverages are also good here courtesy fresh milk on tap.

good place to shack up for remote work when quiet.

reviews.author: Anthony Liew
reviews.text:
Love the service and the atmosphere in this branch. My first time trying this branch of QBistro after moving over 6 months ago.

We love it. And they have baby chair too. And the place is full with families normally as i guess the atmosphere is very good.

reviews.author: irma erliza abdul latif
reviews.text:
Dirty table. Waiter wiped table with dirty wet cloth without using available disinfectant. He just nonchalantly dumped the menu book on the wet smelly table. We had to get tissues to wipe the table ourselves and wipe the sticky wet menu.

We ordered indomie goreng telur mata. Wanted to change it to Telur dadar, but was told that wasn't possible, must take it as is. So we had to order the Telur dadar as a separate item, chargeed rm3.20 for it and on top of that pay for the indomie Telur mata rm6.30 even though we don't want the Telur mata. We agreed to it as we just wanted to eat what we want. But just letting others know that this is my first time a mamak restaurant is unable or maybe unwilling to change the Telur mata to telur dadar because the menu says so.
Another unpleasant experience is we ordered Nasi goreng pattaya. Now almost malaysian knows nasi goreng pattaya has the rice wrapped in the omelette. But the one we got had the omelette laid on top of the fried rice... Take a look at the photo..
when we asked the cashier, he said at Q Bistro the nasi goreng pattaya is like that. No other way without batting an eyelid...
sorry to say, I have been a regular there,but this is the first time I had a very bad experience there. Makes me want to look elsewhere now...

name: Restoran Bintang Kemuning  Subang Jaya
address: 39, Jalan SS 18/1b, Ss 18, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: JEN JAZZEN4
reviews.text:
Nice clean cozy interior. Well maintained.
Breakfast nasi lemak banjir wasnt the curry or soup on rice, rather "soft boiled" egg "bajir" on top of the rice.

Mee siam decent, for none fussy foodies. Probably they will do better taste liken to Melaka. >

reviews.author: Adeline Yeong
reviews.text: First famed for their charred Beef Noodles in Kota Kemuning. Now they expanded to another branch in Subang and they offer more variety to their menu. Came for their tea-break set which consist of a set of half boiled eggs, nasi lemak and a coffee/tea. Food was alright overall.

reviews.author: Wyvern Thin (Wyvern)
reviews.text:
Restaurant Bintang Kemuning in Subang is a culinary gem offering a delightful mix of Chinese and Western cuisine. I've been dining here for many years, and the food has never disappointed.

 Branch Locations:
 Subang Jaya (SS18)
 Kota Kemuning
 Damansara Uptown

My favorites include the Spaghetti Carbonara, Spring Onion Ginger Beef Kuey Teow, Fried Rice (with Wok Hei), and YinYong Noodle. Each dish is bursting with flavor and cooked to perfection. If you havent visited Restoran Bintang Kemuning yet, make sure to try the Spring Onion Ginger Beef Kuey Teow - you wont be disappointed!

name: Peppercorn Cafe
address: 21, Jalan SS 15/4, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Mk Liu
reviews.text:
One of my favourite places to go for western breakfast when I am around Subang. I usually order the American breakfast which is RM15++.

It comes with coffee or tea. You get to choose your egg, either fried egg, omelette or scrambled eggs. I've tried both omelette and scrambled eggs. Both also fluffy and yummy.

You get to choose the side dish too. Chicken ham, sausage, beef bacon or mushrooms.

I love the hash brown too. Very cripsy. Go early on weekends if you want to have breakfast as it might get crowded  sometimes. Breakfast set is from 7:00am to 11am.

Photos are from two recent visits.

reviews.author: Sek Munn Choy
reviews.text:
Lovely establishment serving Western styled deli fare which is almost a landmark of sorts for locals around the area. The menu since then has been carefully curated and tweaked to the current goodness. There's a welcomed hint of local condiments and flavours in the seasoning added to the dishes ordered.

We tried some of the weekend dinner sets which were very good value for what it offered. The grilled chicken set was just right in the amount and cooked just right, no doubt a testament to the experienced kitchen crew. It was all in all a very satisfying dinner outing here which is also a fond throwback to my youth growing up around this area.

reviews.author: Jennifer Wen
reviews.text: 21.02.2025 Friday me and mom reached 730am. It's easy to get parking at this time. The restaurant was comfortable and nice to sit in. My first time here. We shared the flat white coffee and Tuna croissant. The coffee taste wasn't as strong as what the server said it would be if I chose this. I like that the tuna was given generously on the croissant. Tuna tastes good. The croissant thought it was a little hard on the outside and the inside. I was hoping the outside was lightly crisped and fluffy on the inside. The fries were good and nice. Everything cost RM28.60.

name: Coops' Restaurant and Bar
address: First Floor, 12, Jalan SS 12/1b, Ss 12, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Joseph Teoh
reviews.text:
Had a drink at this place on a Monday evening. Quite quiet as only myself and another table of 1 person. Very good environment with snooker, big area with good and windy scenery.

Staff was good and drink was also great. Overall good experience.

reviews.author: Sek Munn Choy
reviews.text:
Part of the Windmill restaurant located downstairs, Coops' has a bar and bar type features not found at the restaurant downstairs. There's pool and large display screens when live games are being broadcasted.

The menu however, is more or less identical since they share a common kitchen. Which is very very good indeed. This means the great grub on the menu can now be enjoyed with a pint of fresh pilsner beer by the Carlsberg brewery. Excellent. Come by early before eight and there's happy hours for certain drinks. All in all, a highly enjoyable evening out here.

reviews.author: Ophilia Ophilia Aquamarine Aquamarine
reviews.text: The air-conditioning wasn't working. Too warm indoors. Service was a bit slow, compared to there weren't many people within the bar. Not a full house. Kinda pricy for our likings.

name: Korean House Restaurant
address: 3A, Jalan SS 15/5a, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

name: Boleros Restaurant
address: No 23A, 1st Floor, Jalan SS 15/5a, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Kavinish Wary
reviews.text:
Dropped by Boleros in SS15 last month had a really good time. The vibe is super chill, with good music and a nice atmosphere just perfect for a hangout thats not too loud or too packed.

Service was quick, we had the creamy cajun pasta, mutton varuval pizza, a chicken burger, and later added a small bucket of popcorn chicken when we decided to stay for a few more drinks! Everything was flavourful and the portion sizes were just nice, not too big and not too small.

Theyve also got this solid Gin OClock promo from 3pm to 9pm where you can get gin based drinks for just RM13-RM14 which is honestly such an amazing deal!

Parking can be difficult, but there are valet guys around so you can just hand over your keys and go enjoy your night.

Highly recommend if you're looking for relaxed spot with good food and very affordable drinks! Will definitely go again!

reviews.author: Yanesha Melissa
reviews.text: The food was delicious, beautifully presented, and full of flavor. A big shout-out to our waiter, Abbas, who was friendly, attentive, and made our dining experience even better. He really took the time to recommend the best dishes and ensured we were well taken care of throughout the meal. I highly recommend this place and will definitely be returning!

reviews.author: Jake Chin
reviews.text:
The service were alright. The guy that served  was from Pakistan. While the owner is an Indian. Came here for dinner. The main meal was alright. However, the side dishes is a must try! I love the sweet potato fries. They come with a sauce for dipping. The buttermilk chicken is also delicious, especially if you serve garlic bread to eat with it.

The reason for 4 star is because the main meal arent my favorite. But, the side dishes are really good.

name: Family Cafe
address: 1, Jalan Pengaturcara U1/51, Kawasan Perindustrian Temasya, 40150 Shah Alam, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Nurin Husna
reviews.text: BAD. Very bad. I put here comparison between their display picture versus what we got today. So disappointed with the big breakfast. What is this? Its not even eye pleasing to eat. Looks like a very lazy person that just want things to be done. Very lazy cooking. Dont come here. Picture and real not same at all. And who on earth give fried mushrooms and who on earth fry cheap sausage for big breakfast. 2 fried eggs instead of scrambled eggs. The sausage is hard and taste worse. I wouldnt come again.

reviews.author: Arif Zakaria
reviews.text:
Trust me if i can leave a review WITHOUT any star - I would have done that.

Waited an HOUR - ONE HOUR for a dry noodles with crispy chicken on 24/7/23 lunch time.

I approach the staff multiple times - he said the order in midst of preparing. If he had inform me that I need to wait for an hour for my meal - i would have walk out to another store.

Inform the reason only 2 staff working. Before he said this the kitchen door open and there are 4 people in side. Doing what I dont know ..

To come again for lunch here - definitely a no no already.

reviews.author: Doreen Ong
reviews.text:
There is not much options for us here in UOA shah alam, so pan family is always full house during lunch time because their food considered okay compared to the foodcourt.

But I was dissapointed that my recent visit to Pan Family I ordered black pepper chicken with rice. The chicken came in sizie smaller than my palm! On top of that it had sour taste, like spoilt meat! I returned the food to them and asked them to check, came back after 30 mins with new meal but I was already full for having to wait long.

My colleague ordered hor fun, the fishballs tasted sour too! She ended up eating just hor fun with the minced chicken.

I think Pan Family should consider some proper handling in keeping their meat / frozen items.

name: Restoran Penang Asam House  SS15
address: 11-G Jalan, Jalan SS 15/8b, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: zhizhi rose
reviews.text:
THE WORSE!! ss15 btw. RM18.90 for fish and chips, but got scammed! Weve never seen that kind of fish and chip that comes with no sauce, until we asked for it  and its so dry? It has to be frozen considering the size and look + taste. This is the second time we've come here, and it's still disappointing. All the food was bad. The hokkien noodles taste nothing, and plain comes with all the FROZEN seafood. Bihun was really bad too, its overcooked and bland. The mineral RM2 for the URO brand. We can get a spritzer for the same price. Chicken chop IS SOGGY and inside taste like frozen food, its not even crisp as it looks. Pictures were a scam.

Also, the first time we came here, the noodle beef, beef tasted fishy. The popia was uncooked, and the second time was worse.

reviews.author: Fyqa Yunus
reviews.text:
Price is affordable. Portion also ok.
The dry asam pedas was good. It had enough flavor to describe asam pedas. The spiciness just nice. Would definitely come again to try the asam pedas.

But maybe can improve for the staff to be a lil bit attentive. Need call for few times only to get response despite less people in the shop.

reviews.author: darluvcas
reviews.text:
Awesome curry, buttermilk and Noodles ....

Finished them all up... tasty food  

Ordered an extra rice just to go with the meat...

For the icecendol, it was nice, just the red bean turned sour, otherwise it was perfect

This place is underrated,  and should try the noodles

Price are really affordable too

name: Canai 15 Cafe, Taste Of India Ss14
address: 99, Jalan SS 14/1, Ss 14, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Jayanaga Sri (Jaya)
reviews.text: This caf is my go to spot for breakfast and lunch, especially if Im craving Indian food. They serve a variety of dishes, but my all-time favourite is their briyani with lamb always rich in flavour and perfectly cooked. What I really appreciate is that if im in the mood for something lighter or vegetarian, theyve got plenty of vege dishes to choose from, all packed with taste. In the evening, they also offer traditional local kuih, which is a nice touch for tea time. Overall, a solid choice for hearty meals and variety. Lulus JPJ!

reviews.author: Surinder Kaur
reviews.text: Its a very Quality food and not forgetting shop cleanliness, the results of strong team and the pretty lady boss. Been here since they open, they have the most variety for vegetarian dishes and to die for curries and Pulicheer keerai. I love coming here in the morning after drops my kids it  feel so calm and good energy. Don't miss the Bru Coffee and Tea Tarik  too. Bravo to the management team.

reviews.author: Yashiny Sweetie
reviews.text: The taste of food Wise i will recommend so delicious, specially chetinad chicken varuval and pulicha kerrai was amazing, but when i had  mutton a bit, vege and kembong fish the price was dispointed RM29, before this i had mutton with chicken just Rm15 only. I dont understand the Service guy put the price like that only. Its Make me very dispointed

name: Hanbing Korean Dessert Cafe (Subang Jaya)
address: G-09, GUARDIAN, Jln SS 15/4G, Ss 15, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Choco Vanilla
reviews.text: The specialty of this place is the shaved ice dessert, which is absolutely delightful. It's flavorful and refreshing without being overly sweet, making it a perfect treat. Highly recommended for dessert lovers! On the other hand, the kimchi fried rice, despite its vibrant and spicy appearance, lacks the heat one might expect. As someone who enjoys bold and spicy flavors, I found it a bit underwhelming and wouldn't recommend it if you're a spice enthusiast. Overall, it's a great spot for dessert, but the savory dishes might not hit the mark for everyone, especially those craving a real spicy kick.

reviews.author: MW
reviews.text:
Very chill atmosphere on weekday evenings. Always love their desserts but the selection has decreased a lot.

Wheres the beloved green tea gone?

The blueberry cheesecake bingsu rm28++ is good and their cheesecake served little warm and goey rm38++ but rather pricey.

However the torched smore bingsu doesnt live up to its standards tho. Would rate that 4/10. Personally find it rather carcinogenic toxic with the burnt smell and weird after taste.

The staffs could be more attentive towards the cutleries given as it has some leftover stains from previous patrons. Service wise is ok.

reviews.author: gary ong
reviews.text:
Came here for shaved ice desserts and surprisingly the red bean paste on top was spoilt and sour.
Told the staff about it and she was unhappy, threw the spoilt red bean paste and gave a new one.
No apology for their spoilt food, as if it was not their issue.
Luckily the shaved ice in general tasted okay.

From my last picture you can see my picture was taken on the 27-Dec, just less than a month ago and you are saying its not available for months? Maybe thats why your red beans were sour.

name: Restoran Good Taste |  | Subang Jaya Branch
address: 36, Jalan SS 14/2, Ss 14, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: Lau Guan Zhen (Sean)
reviews.text:
Restaurant have huge variety of food from rice to noodle dishes. Food taste is quite flavourful and good with well portion. Duck and char siew marinated well and meat odd tender.
We came around 6pm but have to wait half hour only for food to be served and have to takeout as rushing for something. They accept lot of food delivery order as well and probably cause the waiting time is long.

reviews.author: Deadpool
reviews.text: Air conditioning eating place. The sitting area is not crampy. Staff are all foreigners, not too friendly & not all wear masks. Food is all tasty except half boil eggs is atcually 3/4 cooked. Payment at cashier counter.

reviews.author: Love Food
reviews.text: To the chef, please kindly check your curry mee soup base. Its more like a bowl of milk than a bowl of curry. The so call fish cake is selling at RM3.20/pc which I think is expensive. Food taste standard dropped massively.

name: Kafe Bawang Merah
address: 12A, Jalan SS 12/1b, Ss 12, 47500 Subang Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia

reviews.author: M Low
reviews.text:
When waiting for the SJMC tests to come out, it's either here or the mamak next door.
5/2/25 Mee goreng. Omg, too spicy  Should have a warning sign....is this noodle goreng with chili padi? Even considered spicy for a healthy person and totally unbearable for someone feeling unwell. RM3.50

Kuih is the favourite. Small but delicious. RM1.30 per piece. kuih kaswi, gula hangus, Seri muka and cucur udang.

reviews.author: Shiro Kuro
reviews.text: The food and service is average. But the employee is friendly and gives a smile to most of the customers. The place is clean and cozy, a bit tight on some space. There was an outdoor and indoor space to your choosing. However, the food is a mix of good and bad (Roasted chicken was dry, but Ayam masak lemak cili padi is great).  The kuih is great and delicious. The price is reasonable and it is a great place for a drink and talk.

reviews.author: Peggy Chow
reviews.text:
The food are good, i took the beef rendang and it didnt disappoint. The beef are a bit chewy, and the curry is flavourful.
The cokodok is nice too, crispy on the outside, soft on the inside.

However the place is quite small and itll have long q during lunch hour, the parking is nightmare too.
